<br>
Theives combat skills (especially attacks per round) advance much slower than fighters and the fighter hybirds.  Infact, they advance at the same rate as the bard.  So from a realism point of view it makes no sense that EQ rogues should have double attack.  For people wanting EQ rogues to be more like traditional rogues, here is a solution:  no more double attack skill, and add all the traditional theif skills that are missing.  This would include some form of tracking and a skill that will allow rogues to recieve more information about mobs or people that they consider (after all, theives are an information gathering class)  this could include a more defined level range, and noticing some strengths or weaknesses of the mob (all from right clicking a mob). (this would help with the thiefs role as scout)  Also verant could make pick locks and disarm traps a more necessary skill in day to day playing.<br>
<br>
These changes would defiently put the EQ rogue closer to the traditional rogue.  But how many rogues would give up double attack?  Not many I would imagine.  Sadly, most people are more concerned with the power of their class rather than the realism. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kokopelli>Kokopelli</A> at: 4/4/02 10:25:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucalyxto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calyxto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 1:51:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23090.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tracking</span><hr size=1> Given that Tracking is widely considered the class defining skill for Rangers, I think it would be a bad idea to start giving it to more classes. Of course as someone noted already, if I could sneak while hiding and get success/failure messages, then by all means give Rogues Tracking. <p><font face ="Arial" size="2"><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56856">Calyxto Chaos</a></b><br>
