<br>
Jolt can be resisted and it commonly is resisted in battles where a ranger needs to jolt.<br>
<br>
A ranger can be oom, and thus not be able to cast it.  Rangers do not have the mana pool that a real caster has and can get oom real quick.<br>
<br>
Jolt lowers a ranger to just below the top person on the hate list (at least this is what all the rangers say, i'm not the coder so can't say for sure).  My rogue seems to get lowered a lot more than that on the hate list.<br>
<br>
There are plently of skills only rogues get.  Well bards get a lot of them too, but those pesky bards get a lot of everyone skills.  But where bards don't step on rogue toes because pick locks is capped so low they can't open any useful doors,  even their skill cap of 60 does infringe on rangers.  A skill of 60 gives them enough range to track most indoors zone.<br>
<br>
As a ranger, i agree with a previous poster that i'm pissy that anyone gets track besides rangers.  It is about the only thing ppl seem to believe we can bring to a group, we get to be the rare spawn-o-meter.  The last thing we really need is another class to get track and take away that rare group spot we get.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately the ranger class seems to be the laughing stock of Norrath.  I would hope some of you rogues who existed before evade worked could understand how we feel.  You may not have been useless, as rangers are not useless, but the truth does not matter.  What everyone believes is all that matters.<br>
